gomodel:SYNGO_2123  a     owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Rationale: Fig.1F The authors do not mention the postsynaptic density themselves. However, PSD localization is observed by the annotator and referenced to this paper by other authors too (f.i. pmid:26969129)\n\n11/12/2017 Pim\n- The authors mention interaction with Shank3 (a known constituent of the PSD) and to act on AMPAR recycling. This strengthens the claim on postsynaptic localization.. Experimental description: EM: \"Brains from male Sprague Dawley rats were dissected and fixed by immersion with PBS containing 4% PFA and 0.5% glutaraldehyde for 24 h at 4°C....\"\n\nIP: \", Coimmunoprecipitation experiment performed in brain lysate prepared from E18.5 mice, .,...\"\n\nAnnotation made on rat species based on the immuno-EM data." ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2286-1587" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-4973-5732" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2514-0216" ;
        dc:date           "2017-12-11" ;
        dc:title          "SYNGO_CC_2123" ;
        pav:providedBy    "https://syngo.vu.nl" ;
        biolink:in_taxon  "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/NCBITaxon_10116" .
